www.abdn.ac.uk%2Fsociology%2Fnotes07%2FLevel5%2FSO5512%2FWeek%25204%2520%281%29.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWorld+polity+theory\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-lechner-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-lechner_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lechner_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lechner_4-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lechner_4-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lechner_4-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Frank J Lechner; John Boli, eds. (2011). <i>The Globalization Reader</i> (Fourth ed.). Wiley-Blackwell. p.&#160;49. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0470655634\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0470655634\">978-0470655634</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Globalization+Reader&amp;rft.pages=49&amp;rft.edition=Fourth&amp;rft.pub=Wiley-Blackwell&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.isbn=978-0470655634&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWorld+polity+theory\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-boli3-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-5\"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-boli3_5-6\"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite cla